{#
  Contribution Template
  =====================
  Research contribution structure: Gap, Design, Evaluation, Impact.
  Emphasizes identifying knowledge gaps and demonstrating contribution.

  Required Variables:
  - title: Paper title
  - author: Author name(s)
  - abstract: Paper abstract

  Optional Variables:
  - gap: Knowledge gap identification content
  - design: Solution design content
  - evaluation: Evaluation content
  - impact: Impact and implications content
  - date: Publication date (defaults to \today)
  - bibliography: Bibliography file name (defaults to 'references')

  Usage:
    const context = {
      title: "A Novel Approach to X",
      author: "Contributing Author",
      abstract: "This paper contributes...",
      gap: "Current literature lacks...",
      design: "Our design addresses...",
      evaluation: "We evaluated through...",
      impact: "This advances the field by..."
    };
#}
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{hyperref}
\usepackage{amsmath}
\usepackage{graphicx}

\title{{ '{' }}{{ title | texescape }}{{ '}' }}
\author{{ '{' }}{{ author | texescape }}{{ '}' }}
\date{{ '{' }}{% if date %}{{ date | texescape }}{% else %}\today{% endif %}{{ '}' }}

\begin{document}
\maketitle

\begin{abstract}
{{ abstract | texescape }}
\end{abstract}

% Contribution Thesis Structure: Gap, Design, Evaluation, Impact
% This structure emphasizes identifying knowledge gaps and demonstrating contribution

\section{Gap}
{% if gap %}{{ gap | texescape }}{% endif %}

Identification of the knowledge gap in existing literature, establishing the motivation and necessity for this research contribution.

\section{Design}
{% if design %}{{ design | texescape }}{% endif %}

Design of the contribution addressing the identified gap, including methodology, theoretical framework, and implementation approach.

\section{Evaluation}
{% if evaluation %}{{ evaluation | texescape }}{% endif %}

Rigorous evaluation of the contribution, demonstrating its effectiveness in addressing the knowledge gap through empirical validation.

\section{Impact}
{% if impact %}{{ impact | texescape }}{% endif %}

Discussion of the broader impact and implications of this contribution to the field, including future research directions.

\bibliographystyle{plain}
\bibliography{{ '{' }}{{ bibliography | default('references') }}{{ '}' }}

\end{document}
